1. I wasn’t sure what to think when coming up to see you the first time, and when we first started corresponding, I thought you were just being nice/friendly to me. I did think I should plan for staying over that 1st night, though, because I did want to drink (so I could relax, since I was nervous) and not drive. Once there, I definitely got a non-friendly vibe as the evening went on, so I made a pass at you to be sure.
2. I don’t care if you have sex with other people, and if you want to tell me, you can, if you don’t want to tell me, that’s fine, too, it’s solely up to you and your comfort level. I don’t own you, you don't report to me, and I want you to do what you want as long as you’re happy and safe. Also, I know you’d tell me if sex had ever been unsafe, so we could be careful from that point on until we hit the safe zone again, but that wouldn't be a dealbreaker to me in the slightest.
3. Unfortunately, yes. As soon as I am in a relationship, I change, and not for the better – I’m not being dramatic, it’s the truth. After about 12+ attempts of this, I finally decided that I simply don’t like feeling like someone owns me, nor do I like feeling like I own someone else, which unfortunately, is what happens, and it causes my head to get twisted up into all the things I mentioned last night – jealousy, drunken blackout badness, the desire to be free, the introversion time and resentment if I don’t get it, and just the general sense my life is no longer my own. One thing I did mention is the sex also reflects this, and my sex drive pretty much dies because it feels like a duty and not like fun. My last relationship began self-destructing as soon as we ceased being casual and ended up becoming boyfriend-girlfriend, and I couldn’t ignore the fact that the few months where we were casual were fantastically relaxed, and as soon as it became official, a lot of strange mental chains starting wrapping around things.
So I hope this helps and is clear. I enjoy being with you, and I feel we have some kickass times, I just want you to know where my head is at without any confusion.
